# UI guidelines (K-Lab SSO Shell)

Follow [docs/ui-guidelines.md](docs/ui-guidelines.md) for the full reference. Apply when editing views, components, or styles.

## Styling & tokens

- Prefer **Tailwind utility classes** over inline styles, custom CSS, or dynamic class strings unless technically required.
- Use **`@k-lab/components`** defaults; avoid overriding component styles unless design requires it.
- Use **semantic tokens** from `app/globals.css` (`background`, `foreground`, `muted`, `border`, `success`, `warning`, `destructive`, etc.) — no hard-coded hex, radii, or shadows.

## Spacing & RTL

- Use Tailwind’s **4px spacing scale** (`gap-4`, `p-2`, `px-6`, `py-8`); avoid arbitrary spacing unless layout demands it.
- Use **logical** direction: `start`/`end`, `ms-*`/`me-*`, `ps-*`/`pe-*`, `text-start`/`text-end` — not `left`/`right`, `ml-*`/`mr-*`, `pl-*`/`pr-*`, `text-left`/`text-right` unless intentionally fixed-direction.

## Components & layout

- Prefer **`@k-lab/components`** before new local components; compose instead of duplicating with minor tweaks.
- Consistent page structure (header, actions, filters, content); responsive **flex/grid**; test with sidebar open/closed — use **container queries** when width depends on shell chrome, not only viewport.

## States, forms, tables

- Data views: **loading, empty, error, success** — skeletons for cards/charts; spinners for heavy tables.
- Forms: **`FloatingLabelInput`** over raw HTML or plain `Input`; clear required indicators and actionable errors.
- Tables: shared **DataTable** patterns; filters in accordions; consistent loading/empty/error.

## Accessibility, icons, copy

- Semantic HTML; keyboard-accessible controls; don’t rely on color alone; ARIA/labels on icon-only buttons, dialogs, nav.
- **Lucide** icons at consistent sizes; support content, not decoration.
- Clear user-facing copy; no backend jargon; action-oriented button labels.

## Code quality in UI

- Readable JSX; shallow conditionals; extract repeated UI; keep presentation separate from data/business logic.
